# Codex Orchestration Template - Quick Rules

Documentation Map
- AGENTS.md — System architecture, orchestration, tools, usage
- CONTRACTS.md — Compact operating contract + testing

Available Tools
- Local-first LLM gateway (`scripts/llm_gateway.*`)
- Smart routing wrapper (`scripts/codex_wrap.sh`)
- Drive sync (`scripts/sync_to_drive.sh`)

Command Patterns
- Call local model:
  bash -c "cd <your-project-root> && ./scripts/codex_wrap.sh --local 'prompt'"

- Write files:
  Use bash heredoc from your terminal

- Test code:
  bash -c "cd <your-project-root> && <runtime> file"

Critical Rules
1. Use local model first; API fallback only when needed
2. Be diff‑aware; avoid no‑op writes
3. Exclude heavy dirs from sync (node_modules, venv, .git)
4. Keep scripts UTF‑8 + LF

Orchestration Workflow
Request → Route (local/API) → Generate → Write → Test → Iterate

